sentences: Jill Paquette-DeZwaan (born 1979) is a Canadian folk musician and Christian pop singer.
She launched her music career in 2003 with her first studio album, Jill Paquette, released by Reunion Records.
Jill Paquette-DeZwaan was born in Houston, Canada in 1979.
Raised in a musical family, Paquette first played piano at age three and began taking classical lessons that extended into her teenage years, eventually learning to play guitar as well.
An impromptu performance during an open-mic night at a local coffeehouse during her first year led her to join a band fronted by classmate Matt Brouwer.
